{
  "texts": [
    "This exploration investigates performance on cross-lingual tasks.",
    "During the construction of certain general instruction fine-tuning datasets, multiple methods are concurrently employed to leverage the strengths of each, thereby enhancing the datasets' qualities.",
    "The three methods are mentioned in previous sections, and through various combinations, four scenarios can be generated: HG & CI, HG & MC, CI & MC, and HG & CI & MC.",
    "Here, \"HG\" stands for Human-Generated Datasets, \"MC\" for Model-Constructed Datasets, and \"CI\" for Collection and Improvement of Existing Datasets.",
    "(1) While collecting data from other datasets, manual creation of data is concurrently undertaken to supplement missing task types."
  ]
}